$ pdflatex some-document.tex
$ pdflatex some-document.tex

Tada! You're done! You run in twice just to take care of table of content 
issues that can crop up from time to time. But if you're going to push to 
this repo, please do everyone a favor and DON'T push the pdf except for 
release time. Nobody likes repositories that are bloated with TONS of 
binaries when the underlying LaTeX code shows all the real changes.

So, don't push every single change into a pdf. If you want a new pdf in the 
repo, put it in the proper folder:

release/Software-Requirements-Specification-Team-Moon-Moon.pdf
